thread.title: HS roundup: Exeter volleyball wins 5th straight match
thread.title_full: HS roundup: Exeter volleyball wins 5th straight match

author: Staff reports sports@seacoastonline.com
title: HS roundup: Exeter volleyball wins 5th straight match
text: Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 3:13 PM By Staff reports Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 3:13 PM » Social News EXETER — Senior libero Chelsea deRochemont had 45 digs as the Exeter High School volleyball team won its fifth straight match with a 3-1 win over Salem on Wednesday. Exeter, which started the season winless after four matches, is now 5-4 on the season. Individual game scores were 25-23, 25-17, 22-25 and 25-20. Alexis Campbell (eight kills, three aces) and Hanna Schultz (nine kills, three blocks) also starred for the Blue Hawks, who have another home match tonight with Alvirne. Exeter boys see win streak snapped PLAISTOW — It was a disappointing road trip for the Exeter High School boys soccer team on Tuesday. The Blue Hawks (6-2) saw their five-game win streak come to a halt in a 3-0 defeat at Timberlane. The Owls rode their two first-half goals and improved to 8-2 in Division I. Exeter goalies Caden Blazek (three saves) and Jake Spitz (one save) split time, and Exeter was led by senior midfielder Dan Weinhold in defeat. Exeter hosts Alvirne for its 2015 Boys Soccer Youth Day on Friday. Epping boys soccer stuns Derryfield EPPING — AJ Newman (corner kick) and Jackson Rivers (penalty kick) scored the goals, and the Epping High School boys soccer team handed first-place Derryfield its first loss of the season, 1-0, on Monday. Rivers added 10 saves in goal for Epping, which improved to 8-1. The Cougars dropped to 7-1. According to Epping coach Kerry McDermott, it’s the first win for the program against a Derryfield team since 1990, when Newman's father was on the team and McDermott was the assistant coach. Epping volleyball climbs to 7-2 MANCHESTER — The Epping volleyball team defeated Trinity 3-1 on Wednesday and improved to 7-2 in Division III. Individual game scores were 25-17, 23-25, 25-14 and 25-17. Senior Ryen Gallagher had eight kills and six digs for Epping, while senior Olivia Goodrich (five aces, 10 kills, 17 digs, 18 assists), and juniors Sophia Randall (seven aces, five kills, 11 digs) and Emily Colban (15 digs) both chipped in. Mules shoot past Pittsfield NEWMARKET — Morgan Young and Jasmyn Senesombath scored two goals apiece in Newmarket's 6-0 win over Pittsfield on Tuesday, leading the Mules to 8-2 in Division IV. Young opened the scoring in the 12th minute and the Mules got other tallies from Madison Foster, Allie Gallion. Marie Hoehner chipped in a pair of assists and Lauren Moseley was a leader in the midfield. Goalie Anna Valinski earned the shutout in net. Epping girls play Derryfield tough MANCHESTER — In a battle of Division IV unbeatens, it was the Epping High School girls soccer team drawing first blood, but standout Gabi Brummett answered with three goals for Derryfield in a 3-1 win Monday. Evelyn Carleton (from Casey Needham) opened the scoring for Epping 11 minutes in. But Brummett, the two-time Gatorade Player of the Year, scored the last three goals of the game for Derryfield (8-0). Chloe Pelletier made 10 saves for the Blue Devils (8-1), who also got strong games from Sabrina Rivers, and Megan Galante in the midfield; and Meghan Marasca, Brenna Osgood and Erin Killen on defense, according to coach Will Titus. Exeter girls back to .500 EXETER — The Exeter High School girls soccer has found its footing in the Division I standings. Exeter's 1-0 win over Timberlane Tuesday at William Ball Stadium pushed the team to .500 for the first time this season. The Blue Hawks improved to 3-3-2 on the season and are 3-0-1 in their last four games. Exeter traveled to Alvirne on Thursday. By Staff reports
